  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4740",
  "title": "Incorrect behavior on back action of browser history",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nIncorrect behavior of the browser history on back action: User should click twice to get to previous page in browser history.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to `https://instantsearchjs.netlify.app/examples/e-commerce/`\r\n2. Scroll down to pagination and click on second page.\r\n3. After that, click on third page\r\n4. Now try to click on browser's back button - it navigates to previous state (second page) correctly.\r\n5. Try to click on browser's back button again - now it doesn't works correctly. In the result you will be still on the second page instead of first one.\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nUsing browser's back button I expects previous state on each click.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- OS: Linux / macOS\r\n- Browser: any\r\n- Version: instantsearch.js 4.20\r\n\r\n## Additional context\r\n\r\nLook at the flow in `window.addEventListener('popstate', this._onPopState);`. The issue causes because in `AlgoliaSearchHelper.prototype.setState` new instance of SearchParameters is created, so it will be always true for `if (state !== this.state) {` in `AlgoliaSearchHelper.prototype._change`. After that pushState is called.\r\n",
